Content:
A few additions. If you know the width and height of the element, centering horizontally & vertically can be achieved with one <div> like so:<p>.center-div
{
     height:100px;
     width: 100px;
     position:absolute;
     top:50%;
     left:50%;
     margin: -50px 0 0 -50px; 
}<p>This can be modified for the &#x27;centering at the bottom of the page&#x27; example, but with more efficient code.<p>More challenging is centering the unknown:
<a href="http://css-tricks.com/centering-in-the-unknown/" rel="nofollow">http://css-tricks.com/centering-in-the-unknown/</a>
